	"contentText": "PSCI 2223-100: Intro to IR LECTURE\n  \n  \n  \n    \nKey Course Materials\n\nSyllabus\n    \n\nDownload Syllabus\n\nNote: the syllabus was updated with the 9th (vs 8th) edition of the Mingst textbook on 8/23/25. You may want to grab the updated syllabus if you have an older version. No other changes were made to the syllabus.\nUniversity-mandated syllabus addendum statements\n    \n\nDownload University-mandated syllabus addendum statements\n\n\nAssigned Readings and Schedule\nResearch Report Example Article \"Who Securitizes?\"\n    \n\nDownload \"Who Securitizes?\" + Slides\n    \n\nDownload Slides from the Sept. 24 lecture \nMidterm exam information\n\nMonday, October 13 at 10:10 am on Canvas: exam link. The exam ends at 11 am no matter when you start! \nTopics covered: I.A. Intro; II. A. (Neo)Realism; II.B. (Neo)liberalism; and II.C. Marxism. \nUse the lecture slides\n    \n\nDownload lecture slides as a study guide\n10/8/25 Review session slides\n    \n\nDownload slides \n\n\n\nContact Information\n\nTeaching Assistants (recitation numbers)\n\nIsha Banerjee (103, 104) Isha.Banerjee@colorado.edu\n\nRecitations 103 and 104 Google Drive\n    \n\nLinks to an external site. \n\n\nTaufiq Faruque (106, 107) TaufiqE.Faruque@colorado.edu \nGato James (102, 105) Gato.James@colorado.edu \nInbo Park (108, 109) Inbo.Park@colorado.edu \nFurkan Sumbul (101, 112) Furkan.Sumbul@colorado.edu ; 101 & 112 Recitation Sections\nSteven Van De Laarschot (110, 111) Steven.VanDelaarschot@colorado.edu\n\n\n Dr. Tir\n\nemail: jtir@colorado.edu \nOffice hours: Mondays 12:30 - 1:30 pm, 226 Ketchum\nweb site: https://sites.google.com/site/jaroslavtir\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\n\n\n\n\n\nWriting Resources\n\nFarrell, \"Good Writing in Political Science: An Undergraduate Student’s Short Illustrated Primer\" (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.\nNorlin Writing Center at CU (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.\n\nCU Honor Code\n\nWebsite (Links to an external site.)Links to an external site.\n\n\n\n\n  \n  \n\n",
